<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911217-0048</DOCNO><DOCID>911217-0048.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- NWA Inc.:   Minnesota Legislative Panel   Clears $838 Million in Aid</HL><DATE>12/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   NWA</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>AIRLINES (AIR)</IN><NS>FINANCING AGREEMENTS (FNC)</NS><RE>MINNESOTA (MN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   A Minnesota state legislative panel cleared an importantpart of a $838 million state government aid package for NWAInc.'s Northwest Airlines.   The panel approved $320 million in financing from theMetropolitan Airports Commission, which oversees Minnesotaairports. Northwest had said it had to get the airportfinancing as part of its larger financial package. In return,Northwest plans to build maintenance facilities in Duluth,Minn., and Hibbing, Minn. Yesterday's vote was a last step ingetting the state financing.</LP><TEXT>   The financing was a controversial issue in Minnesota amongsome groups which considered the financing package a statebailout of Northwest, which was bought in a 1989 leveragedbuy-out by a group led by Los Angeles investors Al Checchiand Gary Wilson.   Northwest officials have said they plan to use some of thestate financing to pay down part of the debt acquired in thebuy-out. Bankers Trust New York Co. was the lead bankfinancing the buy-out.</TEXT></DOC>